headline: 'The proposed tax on France's highest net worths could reduce the deficit by €5 billion, not €20 billion'
description: Seven economists, including Philippe Aghion, Christian Gollier and Emmanuelle Taugourdeau, say in an op-ed for Le Monde that the 'Zucman tax' would not yield the expected revenue and would face legal, economic and behavioral obstacles.

headline: French borrowing costs soar after PM falls
description: The yield on 10-year French bonds rose to 3.48% on Tuesday, compared to 3.47% for Italian bonds, traditionally the worst in Europe.

headline: French startup Mistral raises €1.7 billion, cementing AI lead in Europe
description: Mistral raised €1.7 billion on Tuesday and sealed a partnership with Dutch chipmaking giant ASML, doubling the AI startup's valuation to €11.7 billion.

headline: 'If Bayrou fell, it is because he refused the golden rule: first build a majority'
description: Constitutional scholar Denis Baranger views the Bayrou government's fall as the logical outcome of 'one man's pretension' to govern 'without a majority or a program.' Resolving the crisis will require going back to the parliamentary system's mechanisms.
